Karma Kameleon


04 Jun 2019 17:08







I like black and white

Dream in black in white

You like black and white

Run runaway

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

SpoilersAround!

SpoiledAway!


SCP-4229 is alive, a memette. The episodes were originally wholesome, and cheerful, but when Karma Kameleon was re-sold to Oliver Brothers Inc. to turn it into an imagination-killer, the content of the episodes began to change. The , representing the memette's original purpose. Karma Kameleon, the character, is a visual representation of the memette, and the final episode, Karma taken from the forest and put in a cage, represents the results of it's torture.

The , half of which affects the human population to this day, was just a side-effect of this whole affair. If every episode had made it to air? Well, 05-4 describes it best.

Props to greytoiletpaper for first commenting on this!



~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

My second article here, after the truly wonderful reception I received for Stalled Conversation. I hope you enjoy reading it!

Image was taken and edited personally.

Big thanks to rattles for a review, If we traded drafts, please let me know!
